      <p class="text-body-lg text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl" data-speakable>
        <strong>Quick answer:</strong> Big Six discharge fees in 2026 run roughly <strong>$260–$340</strong> (TD and Scotia $340; BMO $260). Add provincial registration (~$50–$80) and legal/notary ($500–$1,200). Straight renewals with your current lender have <strong>no discharge fee</strong> — you only pay when you leave. Many new lenders cover most switch costs on promo.
      </p>
